@mariusvniekerk, @lbustelo, @Lull3rSkat3r, do you guys have any thoughts on this? I asked @rdblue to make an issue and PR so we can see if we'd like to include it.

Something I don't like is that our automated `BuildInfo` has been removed in favor of hard-coded values since Gradle cannot take advantage of the generated object from sbt. If we wanted to support a Gradle build, maybe we could have an external config file that Gradle and sbt can load and use when building? We could then either generate the `BuildInfo` class based on the config file or bundle the config file as a resource and change the `BuildInfo` class to read the config file at runtime.

Is anyone interested in this? Too much work to maintain the two? I know that Apache Spark had support for both Maven and sbt (I think they still do), but not sure if it's something we want to consider.

@rdblue, do you have any _pros_ to including this other than you and/or your team are using Gradle?
